parameters.name: amine
parameters.description: Amine nucleophile for amide bond formation

notes.CC(=O)c1ccc(N)cc1: 4-aminoacetophenone - aromatic amine with electron-withdrawing acetyl group
notes.Cc1ccc(CN)cc1: 4-methylbenzylamine - benzylic primary amine with electron-donating methyl
notes.Cc1ccc2cccc(N)c2n1: 8-aminoquinoline derivative - bicyclic aromatic amine, relatively hindered

parameters.name: acid
parameters.description: Carboxylic acid electrophile for amide bond formation

notes.O=C(O)COc1ccccc1: benzodioxole acetic acid - electron-rich aromatic with methylenedioxy group
notes.O=C(O)Cc1ccc2c(c1)C(=O)c1ccccc1CO2: phenoxyacetic acid - simple aromatic ether acetic acid
notes.O=C(O)Cc1ccc2c(c1)OCO2: anthraquinone derivative - complex tricyclic acid, conjugated system

parameters.name: condition
parameters.notes: Each condition is a unique combination of activation reagent, additive, base, and solvent encoded as R##_A##_B##_S##

measurements.name: yield
measurements.description: Percentage yield of amide product (0.0 to 100.0%)

metadata.publication: Intermediate Knowledge Enhanced the Performance of N-Acylation Yield Prediction Model
metadata.analysis_method: HTE with automated liquid handling and LCMS analysis
notes: This is a FULLY MAPPED subset - every amine × acid × condition combination has been tested
No missing data - perfect for optimization algorithm benchmarking
Conditions are pre-packaged combinations - cannot independently vary activation/additive/base
Original data contains 42 activation agents, 11 additives, 8 bases, 1 solvent
This subset contains 72 curated condition combinations from the full space
